# Frontend User Management Feature Template

## Output Contract
- When asked for architecture/design output, include:
  - architecture explanation
  - folder structure
  - design patterns used
  - concrete code examples

## Feature Skeleton
- `features/users/components/UserTable.tsx`
- `features/users/components/UserFormModal.tsx`
- `features/users/hooks/useUsers.ts`
- `features/users/hooks/useUserModal.ts`
- `features/users/api/getUsers.ts`
- `features/users/api/createUser.ts`
- `features/users/schemas/userSchema.ts`
- `features/users/types/user.ts`

## Required Stack Usage
- Server state via TanStack Query hooks.
- Global modal/session UI state via Zustand.
- Forms via React Hook Form + Zod resolver.
- Table via TanStack Table primitives.
- UI base components from shadcn/ui and TailwindCSS.
- Motion interactions via Framer Motion.
- Icons from Lucide.

## Example Integration Flow
- Fetch users in `useUsers` with stable query key `["users"]`.
- Render reusable `DataTable` with sorting/filtering/pagination.
- Open `UserFormModal` from Zustand-backed modal state.
- Validate and submit form with RHF + Zod.
- On success, invalidate `["users"]` query and close modal.

## Scalability Guardrails
- Keep API logic in `features/users/api` or shared `services`.
- Keep component files small and composable.
- Avoid business logic in view components.
- Keep type definitions feature-local unless truly shared.
